Global Product Analyst

Who are we?
Gett is a ride-hailing company and a complex two-sided marketplace with operations in IL, RU, UK and US. Our goal is to provide high-quality reliable service to our customers and become a globally operationally profitable company this year.

As a team we strive to bring impact to the company and grow fast as professionals, thus we base our decisions on data and eager to learn from it’s actual result. Thus Product Analytics team as a global team plays a key role in product definition and further adoption across our markets.

We are looking for people both with business or technical background as our products vary from mobile apps to ml-based algorithms, projects from long term researches which define product strategy to very business-oriented projects together with local teams.

Projects examples:
The majority of our competitor’s losses comes from driver incentives. How to spend this money wisely? Eg, manage campaigns, introduce personalized incentives, link with dynamic pricing on the rider side.
Drivers use our app all day long. What does affect their engagement and retention?
How to set pricing on the market with route optimization algorithm?

What will you do?
Work closely with PMs as a Partner;
Conduct market and product researches;
Analyze features during the product lifecycle: problem research, idea evaluation, success metrics, events definition, business impact follow-up, next steps suggestions;
Manage A/B tests end-to-end starting from formulating hypotheses and design to results evaluation and next steps;
Own an analytical part of a monthly product review meeting, which includes key metrics dynamics, market analysis, feature follow-up (fact impact).

Requirements
Prior experience as a business/product analyst;
Excellent structured problem-solving skills and an ability to use hard data to back up recommendations and develop business cases;
Technical track: excellent Python for data analysis;
Business track: excellent business judgment, strong written and oral communication skills;
Advanced knowledge of SQL;
Strong oral and written communication skills in English;
Prior experience in a tech start-up is a strong plus.
